description:
The closure-literal body-spec resolution pattern appears 4 times identically.
Each copy: reads a ClosureLit from fn_types, pads/truncates a key, calls spec_registry.resolve.

DUPLICATE SITES (all do the same thing):
  ~line 2467: inside return-type propagation (Term::TailCallClosure arm)
  ~line 2588: resolve_tcc_body_sid closure (already a local closure — hoist it)
  ~line 3027: halt_kind selection analysis
  ~line 4820: TailCallClosure direct dispatch in compile_fn

EXTRACT to a free function (before compile_with_backend):
  fn resolve_tcc_body_sid(
      closure: &Var,
      args: &[Var],
      ft: &FnTypes,
      module: &fz_ir::Module,
      spec_registry: &SpecRegistry,
  ) -> Option<u32> {
      let lit = ft.vars.get(closure)?.as_closure_lit()?;
      let body_fn = module.fn_by_id(lit.fn_id);
      let np = body_fn.block(body_fn.entry).params.len();
      let mut key: Vec<Descr> = lit.captures.clone();
      for av in args { key.push(ft.vars.get(av).cloned().unwrap_or_else(Descr::any)); }
      while key.len() < np { key.push(Descr::any()); }
      key.truncate(np);
      spec_registry.resolve(lit.fn_id, &key).map(|s| s.0)
  }

Replace all 4 sites with a call to this function.
Place 2 (the existing local closure) is already named resolve_tcc_body_sid — hoist it to module scope
and replace its 2 internal call sites.

cargo build must produce zero warnings. All tests must pass.
